==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in the 1690s. From {{der|en|ML.|abyssalis}},<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=11}}</ref><ref name=RHD>{{R:RHCD|page=7}}</ref> from {{der|en|la|abyssus||abyss}} + {{m|la|-alis||-al}}.<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976|page=9}}</ref> Equivalent to {{suffix|en|abyss|al}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/əˈbɪs.l̩/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/əˈbɪs.l̩/}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɪsəl}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# {{lb|en|archaic}} Belonging to, or resembling, an [[abyss]]; [[unfathomable]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|geography}} Of or belonging to the [[ocean]] depths, especially below 2000 metres (6500 ft): ''[[abyssal zone]]''. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|geology}} Pertaining to or occurring at excessive depths in the earth's [[crust]]; [[plutonic]]. {{defdate|First attested in the late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

